extracted_text: (J) ID Industrial District. The ID Industrial District is established as a district in which the principal use of land is for industries which can be operated in a relatively clean and quiet manner and which will not be obnoxious to adjacent residential or business districts. The regulations are designed to prohibit the use of land for heavy industry, which should be properly segregated, and to prohibit any other use that would substantially interfere with the development of industrial establishments in the district.
llm_outputs.rationale: This section describes the purpose and intent of the Industrial (ID) zoning district, but does not provide specific parking requirements. The input does not contain any information about minimum parking spaces for this district.
